author: Lindsay Murdoch
title: Thomas Keating pleads guilty over Phuket jet-ski tragedy that killed 'soulmate'
text:

US Defence Secretary Jim Mattis and Senator John McCain distance themselves from President Donald Trump's assessment of the media as 'the enemy of the American People'. More videos Boyfriend charged after fatal jet ski accident 
Thomas Keating, the partner of Victorian woman Emily Collie, who was killed when two jet skis crashed in waters off Phuket, will be charged with reckless driving causing death. Vision courtesy: Channel Seven 
Keating has expressed "unbearable sorrow" over the death of Ms Collie, his 20-year-old girlfriend of two years from the north-east Victorian town of Kyabram. 
The jet-ski Keating was riding and one being ridden by Ms Collie collided in waters off Phuket's Kata beach on February 5. Related Content Boyfriend of Thai jet-ski crash victim Emily Collie could face two-year suspended sentence 
"This was a tragic accident. However, I take responsibility for what happened," Keating said in a statement several days after the crash. "And I have decided that the best thing is to accept a charge of reckless driving leading to death. 
"I would like to express my unbearable sorrow at the loss of my soulmate, Emily, who I loved more than anything in this world, as well as my never-ending apologies and condolences to Ian and Sally Collie and the rest of their family." Advertisement 
Police have said they will recommend a suspended sentence because of Keating's grief and confession. 
An autopsy showed that Ms Collie drowned. SHARE
